  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the maiden pleased him,.... Not the king, into whose presence she was not yet introduced, but the chamberlain; her beauty and her behaviour recommended her to him, and he concluded within himself that she was the person that of all would be acceptable to the king: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and she obtained kindness of him: had favours shown others had not: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and he speedily gave her things for purification; as oil, spices, &c. that she might be the sooner fitted to be had into the king's presence: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "with such things as belonged to her; food and drink from the king's table; the Targum interprets it gifts, as chains and royal apparel: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and seven maidens, which were given her, out of the king's house; to wait upon her the seven days of the week, as the same Targum: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and he preferred her and her maids unto the best place of the house of the women; removed her and them to it, which was the most splendid, had large, airy, and pleasant rooms. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and he preferred her and her maids unto the best place of the house of the women; removed her and them to it, which was the most splendid, had large, airy, and pleasant rooms. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
